posts.name: Sam Whitaker
posts.cooked:
Hi there, I’m from Team 3405 in Salem, Utah and our team is trying to implement PathWeaver-generated paths into our autonomous routines this year. This is my first year programming the robot and based on my current knowledge of our team’s history we have only tried to use PathWeaver once before in 2019 and didn’t experience much success. (In essence, we could run some paths but the paths were never run accurately.) I’m not sure I understand the process of “Reading in” a path JSON file yet, so I tried to follow the WPILib Trajectory Tutorial using their linked example to import a JSON file. (NOTE: I was able to get the example s-curve trajectory to successfully run on our robot beforehand)

The code I have compiles and builds successfully, but runs into a “TrajectoryGenerationException” when I try and run the program in Autonomous mode.

Here’s a picture of the path I’m trying to run in case it’s needed: Screenshot 2022-03-27 230944 1670×1040 990 KB

Screenshot 2022-03-27 230944 1670×1040 990 KB

Screenshot 2022-03-27 230944 1670×1040 990 KB

Here’s a copy of the getAutonomousCommand Command in RobotContainer.java: public Command getAutonomousCommand() {

}

And here’s a screenshot of the RioLog: Screenshot 2022-03-27 231555 1078×760 46.9 KB

Screenshot 2022-03-27 231555 1078×760 46.9 KB

Screenshot 2022-03-27 231555 1078×760 46.9 KB

Any tips or help would be appreciated! Thank you, and good luck to you all this year!

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: That error is from generating exampleTrajectory , not from reading the pathweaver json.  Doesn’t look like you’re using exampleTrajectory anywhere, so you can just delete that.

posts.name: Sam Whitaker
posts.cooked: Thank you for the quick response! By deleting that line, I get a “suggestion” saying the TrajectoryConfig line is unused. Don’t I need this to generate the trajectory, or is the JSON already a generated trajectory? (I guess it would make sense if it is, considering what PathWeaver outputs)

AstroUnit001:

or is the JSON already a generated trajectory?

Yeah it is

posts.name: Sam Whitaker
posts.cooked: Cool, thank you! I don’t have access to the Robot right now but as soon as I do I will test this out.
